WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.204
¡Bienvenido de nuevo!

00:00:02.204 --> 00:00:05.012
La última vez viste los comandos de

00:00:05.012 --> 00:00:05.413
fork.

00:00:05.413 --> 00:00:08.222
Ahora veamos qué significan en la práctica:

00:00:08.222 --> 00:00:11.030
una app de base de datos en

00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:11.432
vivo,

00:00:11.432 --> 00:00:12.635
copiada en segundos,

00:00:12.635 --> 00:00:13.438
editada libremente,

00:00:13.438 --> 00:00:16.246
mientras el original no se entera de

00:00:16.246 --> 00:00:16.647
nada.

00:00:17.404 --> 00:00:19.604
Aquí está la configuración:

00:00:19.604 --> 00:00:22.354
un PostgreSQL real con una

00:00:22.354 --> 00:00:24.004
interfaz pgAdmin encima,

00:00:24.004 --> 00:00:26.754
en vivo en el servidor.

00:00:26.754 --> 00:00:29.504
Un fork es un gemelo

00:00:29.504 --> 00:00:32.255
copy-on-write instantáneo de todo eso.

00:00:32.255 --> 00:00:35.005
Los mismos datos al nacer,

00:00:35.005 --> 00:00:37.205
vidas completamente separadas después.

00:00:40.464 --> 00:00:42.303
Meet the app:

00:00:42.303 --> 00:00:42.915
demo-pgadmin,

00:00:42.915 --> 00:00:45.980
a PostgreSQL with a pgAdmin

00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:46.593
interface,

00:00:46.593 --> 00:00:48.431
mounted and running.

00:00:51.431 --> 00:00:53.808
Un repositorio activo.

00:00:53.808 --> 00:00:56.186
Vamos a clonarlo.

00:00:56.690 --> 00:00:58.437
Este es el original,

00:00:58.437 --> 00:00:59.747
en el navegador.

00:00:59.747 --> 00:01:02.368
pgAdmin pide un inicio de sesión,

00:01:02.368 --> 00:01:04.989
porque es la copia de producción,

00:01:04.989 --> 00:01:07.609
y la producción se mantiene protegida.

00:01:30.357 --> 00:01:31.115
Fork it.

00:01:31.115 --> 00:01:33.770
The copy-on-write clone takes seconds regardless of

00:01:33.770 --> 00:01:34.150
size;

00:01:34.150 --> 00:01:36.805
detach returns as soon as the containers

00:01:36.805 --> 00:01:37.184
start,

00:01:37.184 --> 00:01:39.839
while health checks continue in the background.

00:01:40.725 --> 00:01:41.877
Fork hecho,

00:01:41.877 --> 00:01:42.453
iniciando.

00:01:42.453 --> 00:01:45.334
Los datos no se copiaron,

00:01:45.334 --> 00:01:46.486
se compartieron,

00:01:46.486 --> 00:01:49.367
hasta que uno de los

00:01:49.367 --> 00:01:51.095
lados los modifique.

00:01:54.346 --> 00:01:57.190
Y aquí está el pgAdmin del

00:01:57.190 --> 00:01:57.664
fork.

00:01:57.664 --> 00:02:00.508
Sin inicio de sesión esta vez:

00:02:00.508 --> 00:02:02.878
los forks son sandbox desechables,

00:02:02.878 --> 00:02:05.723
así que la barrera se aparta.

00:02:05.723 --> 00:02:07.145
Las mismas tablas,

00:02:07.145 --> 00:02:08.567
las mismas filas,

00:02:08.567 --> 00:02:10.463
pero su propio universo.

00:02:46.212 --> 00:02:47.475
Two repositories now:

00:02:47.475 --> 00:02:49.581
the original and the experiment,

00:02:49.581 --> 00:02:51.686
each with its own containers,

00:02:51.686 --> 00:02:52.107
network,

00:02:52.107 --> 00:02:53.370
and disk view.

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:57.833
La misma máquina,

00:02:57.833 --> 00:02:59.296
dos mundos aislados.

00:03:02.604 --> 00:03:03.443
Done experimenting?

00:03:03.443 --> 00:03:04.701
Delete the fork.

00:03:04.701 --> 00:03:05.959
Seconds to create,

00:03:05.959 --> 00:03:08.475
seconds to throw away — the

00:03:08.475 --> 00:03:10.572
original never knew it existed.

00:03:13.572 --> 00:03:14.107
Eliminado.

00:03:14.107 --> 00:03:16.785
El original siguió funcionando todo

00:03:16.785 --> 00:03:17.856
el tiempo.

00:03:18.643 --> 00:03:21.335
Así que haz fork con

00:03:21.335 --> 00:03:21.873
libertad,

00:03:21.873 --> 00:03:24.565
la producción no puede salir

00:03:24.565 --> 00:03:25.103
perjudicada.

00:03:25.103 --> 00:03:26.180
A continuación,

00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:27.795
veremos los secrets,

00:03:27.795 --> 00:03:30.486
lo único que tus forks

00:03:30.486 --> 00:03:32.101
deliberadamente no heredan.

00:03:32.101 --> 00:03:33.716
¡Nos vemos allí!
